<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph>
[[ 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CF263E47-E7D3-4AE5-9772-5A3D28FE0624" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microglanis Eigenmann 1912:130, 155" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microglanis</taxonomicName>
Eigenmann ]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="32">
The genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CF263E47-E7D3-4AE5-9772-5A3D28FE0624" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microglanis Eigenmann 1912:130, 155" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microglanis</taxonomicName>
was proposed by Eigenmann (1912) to include 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E902F0B2-DB73-4580-B19B-675A40A48FDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microglanis poecilus Eigenmann 1912:155" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="poecilus">Microglanis poecilus</taxonomicName>
and related species of reduced size, reaching a total length of nearly 110 mm (Eigenmann, 1912). This genus is further characterized by the wide mouth (gape same of the head width), short barbels (occasionally reaching pectoral-fin origin), small eyes without free orbital margin, absence of axillary pore, a dark saddle straddling supraoccipital area to the end of dorsal-fin base, pre-maxillary dental plate with rounded margin and thin mesocoracoid arch (Shibatta, 2003a; 2003b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="32">
Fourteen species are valid in the genus, occurring from trans-Andean drainages in Peru and Ecuador, eastward to the Orinoco and Amazon basins and southward to the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="río">rio</normalizedToken>
de la Plata basin, Argentina (Bertaco &amp; Cardoso, 2005; Shibatta &amp; Benine, 2005). 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CF263E47-E7D3-4AE5-9772-5A3D28FE0624" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microglanis Eigenmann 1912:130, 155" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microglanis</taxonomicName>
is also present in the eastern coastal rivers of Brazil, with the following species: 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:88D1CBA0-B876-4F2E-AA0D-8B235C0E8FA1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microglanis cibelae Malabarba &amp; Mahler 1998:249" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cibelae">M. cibelae Malabarba &amp; Mahler-Jr., 1998</taxonomicName>
(rio 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Maquiné">Maquine</normalizedToken>
basin, RS), 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cottoides">M. cottoides (Boulenger, 1891)</taxonomicName>
(rio 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Camaquã">Camaqua</normalizedToken>
basin, RS), 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parahybae">M. parahybae (Steindachner, 1880)</taxonomicName>
(rio 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraíba">Paraiba</normalizedToken>
do Sul basin, RJ) and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7531B5BB-D0FD-4DDB-A0F6-3589B418CED5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microglanis nigripinnis Bizerril &amp; Perez-Neto 1992:97" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigripinnis">M. nigripinnis Bizerril &amp; Perez-Neto, 1992</taxonomicName>
(rio Macacu basin, RJ) (Bizerril &amp; Perez-Neto, 1992; Malabarba &amp; Mahler-Jr., 1998; Shibatta, 2003a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="32">
Samples of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CF263E47-E7D3-4AE5-9772-5A3D28FE0624" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microglanis Eigenmann 1912:130, 155" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microglanis</taxonomicName>
were recently collected in the rio 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Francisco basin. This is an independent hydrographic basin and has an area of 634 km2 (Cunha, 1998), across the Brazilian States of Minas Gerais, Bahia, Pernambuco, Sergipe and Alagoas. The peculiar geomorphologic aspects and the occurrence of endemic species (e.g., 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Conorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conirostris">Conorhynchus conirostris (Valenciennes, 1840)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Duopalatinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emarginatus">Duopalatinus emarginatus (Valenciennes, 1840)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Doradidae" genus="Franciscodoras" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmoratus">Franciscodoras marmoratus (Reinhardt, 1874)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F89D8D67-80A4-420E-A883-CCC96245A16C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Lophiosilurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Lophiosilurus alexandri Steindachner 1876:154 [106]" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alexandri">Lophiosilurus alexandri Steindachner, 1876</taxonomicName>
, among others), suggest an old isolation of the rio 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Francisco system. Examination of specimens of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CF263E47-E7D3-4AE5-9772-5A3D28FE0624" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microglanis Eigenmann 1912:130, 155" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microglanis</taxonomicName>
from this basin reveals that they constitute a new species, with a set of distinctive morphological characters. This new species is described herein.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
